# Image Generation Workflow

When the user asks to generate or regenerate images:

- Before image requests, run a quick capability check for `GenerateImage`.
- If `GenerateImage` is unavailable, warn in one line and instruct the user to switch to an image-capable model for this chat.
- If `GenerateImage` is available, attempt image generation immediately.
- If image generation is unavailable in the current model/session, do not fail silently.
- Tell the user in one line that image generation is unavailable in the current model.
- Ask the user to switch to an image-capable model, then retry the same prompts right away.
- Reuse the latest approved prompts and references from the conversation unless the user asks for changes.
- After generation, replace target asset files in-place (same filenames) so existing site references keep working.
